      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BILLS SWAN SONG (3) started from a wide draw on the front line last start. Pushed forward to settle handy then boxed on gamely and finished a neck from the winner in second at Parkes over 1660m. No excuses from this more advantageous draw. Finds a nice race and can earn a well-deserved victory. SUMMER DELIGHT (7) finished fourth last start over 1609m at Newcastle, beaten 15 metres, after a good win at this track the run prior. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. This looks a sterner test than last time but on her best form she is good enough to take this out. ROCKNROLL BLING (5) is in the mix following a respectable third at his most recent appearance over 1660m at Parkes. YESNOLETSGO (10) after turning in a better effort last start to finish third at Bathurst over 1730m is a must include in combinations.",
